         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Acquisition of a Bluefors LD250 Cryogen-Free Dilution Refrigerator System to The
                  Niels Bohr Institute, University of Copenhagen</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>043-0317-18-7000</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="38000000" />
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES" />
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The equipment will be used for opto-and electro-mechanical experiments at The
                  Niels Bohr Institute, NBI.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="DKK">2900000.00</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION />
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="DK0" />
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="DK011" />
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Niels Bohr Institute is purchasing a cryogen free dilution refrigerator to
                     extend their cryogenic measurement capability to temperatures less than 20
                     milliKelvin.</P>
                  <P>The refrigerator will be used for opto- and electromechanical experiments at
                     The Niels Bohr Institute.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS />
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED />
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
                  <D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE />
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>According to the European Parliament and Council Directive nº 2014/24/ EC,
                        Article 32. 2, point b, the University of Copenhagen believes that Bluefors
                        Cryogenics Oy is the only manufacturer that can meet the following
                        requirements asked for by The Niels Bohr Institute.</P>
                     <P>Due to the nature of opto-mechanical experiments, mechanical vibrations have
                        extremely adverse effect on the measurements. Despite advanced damping
                        systems, the operation of the pulse tube cryocooler required for
                        refrigeration is a significant source of mechanical vibrations and noise in
                        all cryogen free dilution refrigerators. This can make it impossible to
                        perform opto-mechanical experiments. NBI therefore requires the possibility
                        to switch off the pulse tube cooler during the aquisition of sensitive data.
                        Bluefors is offering a so-called Helium battery option integrated in their
                        dilution refrigerator. The battery allows operation of the refrigerator at
                        the base temperature with the pulse tube turned off for a prolonged time
                        long enough to perform sufficient measurement series. Together with the
                        active damping, the Helium battery drastically reduces the mechanical
                        vibrations and noise to a level where opto-mechanical experiments are
                        possible.</P>
                     <P>Bluefors is the only manufacturer offering such an integrated solution that
                        is tested and ready.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
